# Wire-format FRAME snapshot — DO NOT edit by hand.
# File: snapshots/wire_frames.snap
# Each entry is a full Rynk frame — 5-byte header (CMD u16 LE + SEQ u8 + LEN
# u16 LE) + postcard payload — one per protocol message; the label names the
# decoded payload (`()` = empty). A diff means the header, a CMD number, or a
# message frame changed. If intentional, bump ProtocolVersion::CURRENT and regenerate:
#   UPDATE_SNAPSHOTS=1 cargo test -p rmk-types --features rynk wire_frames
# Format: <label>  <hex bytes>

